HEADWORD: broadtail
<hw>broadtail</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the fur of a very
young karakul lamb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a hardy coarse-haired sheep of central Asia; the
lambs are valued for their soft curly black fur.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> caracul, karakul.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

